parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Hydraulic Brake System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to become hard or inoperable, leading to accidents or injuries.
The issues reported are unrelated to the hydraulic brake system recall and do not affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: engine showing signs of potential failure
alternator prematurely replaced due to electrical overcharge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the radio and clock screen turn off and on randomly
and the brake lights remain on when the foot is off the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake lights remain on when the foot is off the brake pedal
the vehicle decelerates and stalls when slowing down
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine compartment fire can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and can also lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while driving or parked
and there is a burning smell coming from the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle has trouble shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
